-- VimpelCom Gains on Plan to Sell Stake in Algerian Joint Venture
-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 2012-01-09T19:42:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/vimpelcom-gains-on-plan-to-sell-stake-in-algerian-joint-venture.html
VimpelCom Ltd. (VIP) ,  Russia ’s second-
biggest mobile-phone operator, rose to a one-month high after it
said it is selling a stake in an Algerian joint venture.  Algeria’s Ministry of Finance agreed to buy a 51 percent
stake in mobile telephone operator Orascom Telecom Algeria,
Zoheir Meziane, an adviser to the Post and Telecommunication
Minister, said yesterday.  VimpelCom gained 2.5 percent to $10.17 at 2:38 p.m. in New
York trading, its highest intraday price since Dec. 12.  Terms of the transaction weren’t disclosed.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York 
